word_mean_info__list.difference: 一般指通过言语或文字或行为表示出的强烈抗议、反对。
指用力量或意志抵抗、制止对方的入侵或诱惑、影响等。
多指因厌恶或反感而反对，但不一定明显地表露出来。
普通用词，含义广，语气强于object。多指反对一些较重大的事，隐含其正当性。
较正式用词，指坚强地抵抗攻击或压力，有时也指抗住影响或吸引力。
指公开地、勇敢地反对或抵抗，有时含公然挑衅之意。
指积极地反抗一种攻击或暴力，或诱惑。
普通用词，可表不同程度的抵抗。

list.abstract: Resist（英 [rɪˈzɪst]，美 [rɪˈzɪst]），英语单词，作动词用，为抵抗；抵御；抵制。作名词用，为保护涂层；防染材料；涂釉层。短语搭配有wax resist（蜡防），例句为“The fly can resist everything that happens around him.（苍蝇可以抵抗周围发生的一切事情。）” Resist不及物动词类近义词有hit back、stick up to，及物动词类近义词有tough、hit back，名词类近义词有reserving agent，相关反义词有lend oneself、surrender。Resist的名词形式为resistance、resistant，形容词形式为resistible、resistive、resistless。

yingyinNormal.en: Nice location for the final act, couldn't have chosen it better myself. But then I never could resist a touch of the dramatic.
yingyinNormal.zh: 最后一幕的绝佳地点，我都选不出更好的。但我向来无法抵抗戏剧化的手笔。

yingyinNormal.en: Pursue us, you'll be caught. Resist us, you'll be killed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 继续追查我们，你会被抓住，跟我们做对，你就会被干掉。

yingyinNormal.en: I can see why that's hard to resist. I like her so much.
yingyinNormal.zh: 难怪你无法抗拒。我好喜欢她。

yingyinNormal.en: Wow, and I can't resist that line. That's why I never wear sweatpants.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我抗拒不了这个诱惑，所以我都不穿运动裤。

yingyinNormal.en: I would resist the temptation to stretch. The temperature around you is well below freezing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我可不会想要伸展。你所处的环境温度不到零度。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm not through yet. I've got something that will make you hand over that formula. Something you can't resist.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我还没完呢。我有一些能让你交出秘方的东西，一些你没有办法抗拒的东西，
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《The SpongeBob Movie: Sponge Out of Water》

yingyinNormal.en: Here, we brought wine. Look at this, it's from the cellars of Ernest and Tova Borgnine, so how could we resist?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们带了一瓶酒，这是来自欧内斯特和托娃博格宁的酒窖（演员和酒类收藏家），我们怎么能够拒绝呢？

yingyinNormal.en: Quit? No. I give them a show they cannot resist, which is gonna be, just one more minute, s'il vous plat. Merci.
yingyinNormal.zh: 退休？不。我要整个轰动全城的节目，你猜是什么？就再等一分钟，好吗？谢谢。

yingyinNormal.en: OK, I think it's safe to turn the beef now. Resist the temptation to turn it too early. You want a gorgeous brown on there.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我觉得现在可以将牛肉翻过来了，一定不要翻早了，要煎成金黄色为止。

yingyinNormal.en: This tank'll get plenty dirty in that time but we have to help it along any way we can. Jacques? No cleaning. I shall resist.
yingyinNormal.zh: 到那时候这个水箱会脏乱不堪，我们要尽量努力搞脏它，虾虾？停止清理，我尽力而为。

yingyinNormal.en: Just try to resist giving him sleeping pills, if possible. They tend to make him a little bit, you know, irritable. No, more irritable.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是尽量别给他安眠药，那会使变得他有点，暴躁，应该说，更暴躁。

word_usage.usage:
resist表示“抵制；阻挡”时，多用作及物动词，接名词、代词或动名词作宾语。例：
They are determined to resist pressure to change the law.
他们决心顶住要求改革法律的压力。
偶尔可用作不及物动词。例：
He could resist no longer.
他抵抗不住了。

当resist用来表达“忍住；抵挡”时，多用于否定句中，意思是“不禁；忍不住”，后面可接动名词，但不可接不定式。例：
他忍不住炫耀起了他的新车。
正：He couldn't resist showing off his new car.
误：He couldn't resist to show off his new car.
